#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:1
msgid "Contributing documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:3
msgid ""
"Thank you for your interest in helping improve documentation in the Nix "
"ecosystem! This project would not be possible without your support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:6
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:8
msgid ""
"Check the overview of [documentation resources](./resources.md). "
"Documentation contributions should follow the [style guide](./style-guide."
"md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:11
msgid ""
"Get in touch with the [Nix documentation team](https://nixos.org/community/"
"teams/documentation) if you need more guidance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:14
msgid ""
"If you cannot contribute time, consider [donating to the NixOS Foundation's "
"documentation project on Open Collective](https://opencollective.com/nixos/"
"projects/nix-documentation) to fund ongoing maintenance and development of "
"reference documentation and learning materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:17
msgid "Feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:19
msgid ""
"Feedback is also a valuable contribution. Please share your thoughts in the "
"[Documentation category on Discourse](https://discourse.nixos.org/c/dev/"
"documentation/25)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:22
msgid "Nix beginners"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:24
msgid ""
"Try to use official documentation as your primary resource, however "
"incomplete it may appear."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:26
msgid ""
"Please open issues and report all problems or questions that arise. Also "
"state your learning goals and the paths you have taken so far."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:29
msgid ""
"Sharing your first-hand experience will help guide our efforts and solve "
"recurrent problems with documentation for you and everyone else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:31
msgid "Nix educators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:33
msgid ""
"You will probably have observed where learners get stuck most often, and "
"which typical needs and questions they have. You may have your own written "
"notes for classes, trainings, or presentations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:36
msgid ""
"Please share your experience to help us improve upstream documentation and "
"beginner materials, so you can focus on providing the best value to your "
"students."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:38
msgid "Domain experts using Nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:40
msgid ""
"If you are proficient in applying Nix to a domain-specific problem, and want "
"to share your expertise on best practices, please check the existing content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:41
msgid "Does existing material on your subject meet your standards?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:42
msgid "How could we improve it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:43
msgid "Is there a popular application of Nix's capabilities not yet covered?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:44
msgid "We would be glad to incorporate your insights."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:46
msgid "Licensing and attribution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:48
msgid ""
"When opening pull requests with your own contributions, you agree to "
"licensing your work under [CC-BY-SA 4.0](https://creativecommons.org/"
"licenses/by-sa/4.0/)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:50
msgid ""
"When adding material made by others, make sure it has a license that permits "
"this. In that case, unambiguously state source, authors, and license in the "
"newly added content. Ideally, notify the authors *before* using their work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:54
msgid ""
"[Add the original author as co-author](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-"
"requests/committing-changes-to-your-project/creating-and-editing-commits/"
"creating-a-commit-with-multiple-authors) to the first commit of your pull "
"request, which should contain the original document verbatim, so we can "
"track authorship and changes through version history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:56
msgid ""
"Using free licenses other than CC-BY-SA 4.0 is possible for individual "
"documents. By contributing changes to those documents you agree to license "
"your work accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/index.md:60
msgid ""
"If you have written a tutorial or guide related to Nix, please consider "
"licensing it under CC-BY-SA 4.0! This will allow us to feature your work as "
"official documentation if it complements or improves upon existing materials."
msgstr ""
